cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper addresses privacy concerns in DNN inference and proposes a method to reduce the information content of communicated data without compromising accuracy. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper presents an end-to-end framework that learns an additive noise distribution to reduce information content while maintaining accuracy. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible category as the paper mentions experimentation with real-world DNNs, which could involve computer vision applications. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as DNNs are a popular AI technique and the paper proposes a method to improve privacy in DNN inference. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the trend toward cloud-hosted inference services and proposes a method to reduce the amount of data sent over the network.
